On the eastern bank of the Chuanhe River in Jingdong Yi Autonomous County, southwest China's Yunnan Province, a stretch of auburn mounds and pillars stand out, making up a dense forest guarding the foot of the Ailao Mountains. This is one of the four unique earth forests in Yunnan, Jingdong Earth Forest. Comprising many earth pillars, the forest presents a special water-eroded landform. About 'Journeys in Nature': Ailao Mountains Series Sitting in the middle of southwest China's Yunnan Province, the Ailao Mountains are famous for their biodiversity. From endangered wild beasts like black crested gibbons and green peafowls to rare plants and various landscapes, the Ailao Mountains will never disappoint you. For more: Ailao Mountains Series | Ep. 8: Misty forest Ailao Mountains Series | Ep. 7: A dynamic valley Ailao Mountains Series | Ep. 6: Red junglefowl Ailao Mountains Series | Ep. 5: Jiutian wetland Ailao Mountains Series | Ep. 4: Flowering cycas Ailao Mountains Series | Ep. 3: Neighbors in the mountains Ailao Mountains Series | Ep. 2: King of birds Ailao Mountains Series | Ep. 1: Phoenix at the river (Cover image a screenshot) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)